lighting their transgressive, transnational and provocative nature. It shows how B-movie Gothic is a relentlessly creative form, filled with political tensions and moving from shocking conservatism to profound social critique.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aB filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aGothic fiction (Literary genre)xInfluence. 0aGothic revival (Literature)xInfluence. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aAncuta, Katarzyna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrowning, John Edgar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöhme, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Justin D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuchs, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöglund, Johan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHöglund, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIbarra, Enrique Ajuria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhair, Tabish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcRoy, Jay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReyes, Xavier Aldana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSyed, Tuǧçe Bıçakçı, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSá, Daniel Serravalle de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWester, Maisha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311078043740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147442345840uhttps